1- From the main menu select file
2- Select Host Network Manager
3- Select create
4- This would create the settings of the new network, check the "Enable DHCP Server". Now go back to network settings it should see the name of the newly created network when you select Host-only Adapter.
With VM powered down

5- Click Settings > Network Click Adapter 1 and choose Bridged Adapter
6- Click Adapter 2 and choose Host Only Adapter
7- Click File > Preferences > Networks Under NAT Networks if you don't see a NAT Network click on + icon to add NAT Network.
8- Click Host-Only Networks if you don't see a host only network click + icon to add one
9- make sure to have 2 network adapters used by the VM machine as one will be used as NAT and the other will be host only.
